 CTE :- 
 ---------
  
 => Common Table Expression
 => using CTE also we can give name to the query output and we can use that name in another query
 => CTE simplifies complex queries
 => using CTE we can break a complex query into multiple queries and later combine outputs 

syntax :-
-------------

  WITH <CTE1>
   AS
      (SELECT statement1) ,
   <CTE2>
   AS
      (SELECT statement2)
   -----------------------------------
   
   SELECT statement ;

 Ex 1  :-   display first 5th row from emp table ?
 ---------
 
 WITH E
  AS
      (SELECT  rownum as rno,empno,ename,sal FROM emp)
 SELECT * FROM E WHERE rno = 5 ; 
                                 WHERE rno IN (5,10,15) ;
                                 WHERE rno BETWEEN 5 AND 10;
                                 WHERE MOD(rno,2) = 0;
                                 WHERE  MOD(rno,2) = 1 ;
                                    
